{"title_page": "Thomas Rhett discography", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist discography\n|Artist        = [[Thomas Rhett]]\n|Image         = Thomas Rhett.jpg\n|Caption       = Thomas Rhett performing in [[Baltimore, Maryland]], on January 24, 2013\n|Studio        = 4\n|Compilation   = \n|Live          = \n|EP            = 1\n|Singles       = 19 <!--Be a Light-->\n|Music videos  = 22 <!--Remember You Young-->\n| Option       = 14 <!--Remember You Young-->\n| Option name  = #1 Singles\n\n}}\n\nAmerican singer and songwriter [[Thomas Rhett]] has released four studio albums, one extended play and 19 singles, including two as a featured artist. His debut album, ''[[It Goes Like This]]'', debuted in the top 10 of the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] in 2013 and produced three number one singles on the [[Country Airplay|''Billboard'' Country Airplay]] chart. Rhett released his second album ''[[Tangled Up (Thomas Rhett album)|Tangled Up]]'' in 2015, which peaked at number six on the ''Billboard'' 200. Four of the album's five singles reached number one on the country charts, while the second single, \"[[Die a Happy Man]]\" became his first [[crossover (music)|crossover]] success and highest-charting single on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. His third album, ''[[Life Changes (Thomas Rhett album)|Life Changes]]'', was released in 2017 and includes the chart-topping single \"[[Craving You]]\". Twelve of Rhett's singles have received at least a Gold [[RIAA certification|certification]] from the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA), with seven going Platinum.\n\nRhett has also written songs for other country artists, and made history in 2013 when half of the top 10 singles on the Country Airplay chart were written by Rhett or his father, [[Rhett Akins]], including the singer's own chart-topping hit, \"[[It Goes Like This (song)|It Goes Like This]]\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Conaway|first1=Alanna|title=Thomas Rhett and Rhett Akins Make Chart History As Family Is Responsible for Writing Half of the Top 10|url=http://www.roughstock.com/blog/thomas-rhett-and-rhett-akins-make-chart-history-as-family-is-responsible-for-writing-half-of-the-top-10|accessdate=September 6, 2017|work=Roughstock|publisher=Cheri Media|date=September 17, 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102064612/http://www.roughstock.com/blog/thomas-rhett-and-rhett-akins-make-chart-history-as-family-is-responsible-for-writing-half-of-the-top-10|archivedate=November 2, 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Studio albums ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Details\n! colspan=\"5\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Sales\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| [[Music recording sales certifications|Certifications]]\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Top Country Albums|US Country]]<br><ref name=\"Country Albums\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/thomas-rhett/chart-history/country-albums |title=Thomas Rhett Chart History (Top Country Albums) |publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=October 23, 2017}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br><ref name=\"Billboard 200\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/thomas-rhett/chart-history/billboard-200 |title=Thomas Rhett Chart History (''Billboard'' 200) |publisher=Billboard |accessdate=October 23, 2017}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br><ref>Peak positions on Australian Albums chart:\n* All except noted: {{cite web|url=http://australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Thomas+Rhett|title=australian-charts.com \u2013 Discography Thomas Rhett|website=australian-charts.com|accessdate=September 22, 2017}}\n* ''Tangled Up'': {{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/aria-albums-parkway-drive-ire-is-australias-no-1-album-20151003|title=ARIA Albums: Parkway Drive 'Ire' Is Australia's No 1 Album|publisher=Noise11|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|date=October 3, 2015|accessdate=October 3, 2015}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/thomas-rhett/chart-history/canadian-albums |title=Thomas Rhett Chart History (Canadian Albums) |publisher=Billboard |accessdate=October 23, 2017}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]<br><ref>http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/31595/thomas-rhett/</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[It Goes Like This]]''\n| \n* Release date: October 29, 2013\n* Label: [[Big Machine Records|Valory]]\n| 2\n| 6\n| \u2014\n| 23\n| \u2014\n|\n* [[Nielsen SoundScan|US]]: 271,000<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hitsdailydouble.com/new_album_releases|title=Upcoming Releases: Hits Daily Double|publisher=Hits Daily Double|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6bmWOyeFj|archivedate=September 24, 2015}}</ref>\n|\n* [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]: Platinum{{Certification Cite Ref |region=United States |artist=Thomas Rhett |title=It Goes Like This |type=album }}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Tangled Up (Thomas Rhett album)|Tangled Up]]''\n| \n* Release date: September 25, 2015\n* Label: Valory\n| 2\n| 6\n| 77\n| 2\n| 80\n|\n* US: 598,900<ref name=\"roughstock sept2017\">{{cite news|url=http://roughstock.com/news/2017/09/42322-top-10-country-album-sales-chart-september-25-2017|title=TOP 10 Country Album Sales Chart: September 25, 2017|last=Bjorke|first=Matt|date= September 27, 2017 |work=Roughstock|access-date=|archive-url=|archive-date=}}</ref>\n|\n* RIAA: 2x Platinum{{Certification Cite Ref |region=United States |artist=Thomas Rhett |title=Tangled Up |type=album }}\n* [[Music Canada|MC]]: Gold{{Certification Cite Ref|region=Canada|artist=Thomas Rhett |title=Tangled Up |type=album }}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Life Changes (Thomas Rhett album)|Life Changes]]''\n|\n* Release date: September 8, 2017\n* Label: Valory\n| 1\n| 1\n| 30\n| 2\n| 54\n|\n* 